column5: I had a goal this year to break LBS this year and I finally did it with a 6.6 lbs large.  The best part was I spent 30 minutes chasing this guy and changed baits 4 or 5 times going down the shore line.  He kept coming out for a peak but would not go away, just went from cover to cover.  Never seen anything like it before. The best part was how clean and healthy he looked, not a mark or scare.
nice fish too bad the pic is a selfie
that is a big fish! Any idea on its length?
length was 22.5 and the girth was 16, it was a football
nice piggy! i'm hoping to run into his cousin on Eels lake this week!

Nice hawg!  I got my largemouth PB in September in the Loring area during the remnants of Hurricane Andrew - it was a great day for bass and for a rain suit.  One of these days, I'll get another PB....  WR
Congrats !!!! Nice hog for sure !!!!!! Cheers
